China’s Sina to Market Weibo Service in Japan via Partnership

-- B y   B e l i n d a   C a o
-- 
2011-06-28T15:42:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/china-s-sina-to-market-weibo-service-in-japan-via-partnership.html
Sina Corp., owner of  China ’s third-
most visited website, entered a partnership with a Japanese
company to market its Twitter-like Weibo service in the world’s
third-biggest economy.  Find Japan Inc.  will provide Weibo account verification
services for Japanese businesses, institutions and celebrities
beginning July 1, Sina News, a news service owned by the Chinese
corporation,  said  in a report on its website. Japanese companies
and individuals will be able to communicate with 140 million
Chinese microblog users through the service, Sina said.  Sina’s shares gained 4.5 percent to $99.09 at 11:38 a.m.
New York time. They earlier climbed as much as 5.9 percent to
$100.35, the highest intraday level in three weeks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Belinda Cao in New York at 
